2026-05-01T20:43:24 [INFO] __main__ - This will be used in Post: What is Devops?
It’s practice of using automation tools in order to improve development process & increase productivity which ultimately reduces costs too by reducing human error as well like manual testing etc. It helps us make changes quickly without compromising quality assurance thus providing reliable products with better customer experience at lower cost than ever before! The main idea behind devops comes from software engineering philosophy called “Continuous Integration” (CI) where all team members work on code simultaneously while continuously integrating new features into existing codebase so that everyone can see what each person has done throughout entire project lifecycle right up until deployment stage when everything gets published publicly online finally getting ready end users access them immediately after launch date announced beforehand :) This approach allows teams collaborate effectively communicate openly build trust within their organization faster cycles iterations hence resulting higher overall performance levels across board! Overall speaking this method brings forth several benefits including quicker delivery time shorter feedback loops improved collaboration efficiency increased transparency among stakeholders reduced waste wastage due less bugs defects detected early stages allowing developers focus more innovating instead debugging problems later down line journey life cycle roadmap path way forward future growth plans strategic vision goals objectives milestones targets aims aspirations dreams ambitions hopes desires wishes prayers blessings gratitude love compassion kindness understanding empathy patience tolerance wisdom knowledge expertise skill proficiency mastery learning education training coaching mentoring guidance support assistance help advice counsel instruction direction leadership management supervision control oversight monitoring evaluation assessment review analysis report recommendation decision making planning organizing scheduling b